			"value":"<p class=\"flavour\"><i>When extra effort is called for, your chaos-touched being cannot help but respond.</i></p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Encounter âœ¦ Elemental</b></p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Free Action</b><b> &#8226; </b><b>Ranged</b> sight</p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Trigger:</b> You or an ally you can see spends an action point to make an attack. </p><p><b>Effect:</b> After the attack is resolved, roll a d6. The triggering character gains the resulting benefit. </p><p>1. The character gains a +2 power bonus to attack rolls until the end of your next turn. </p><p>2. Until the end of your next turn, the target of the attack takes 2 extra damage each time it is hit with an attack. </p><p>3. The creature gains a +2 power bonus to speed until the end of your next turn. </p><p>4. Until the end of your next turn, the target of the attack grants combat advantage. </p><p>5. The character can make a basic attack as a free action. </p><p>6. Until the end of your next turn, the target of the attack cannot shift. </p><p>Published in Dragon Magazine 408. </p>",
